### Area

testsuite

### Describe the bug

With the new test framework, I have ..

```
@KeycloakIntegrationTest
public class OID4VCIWellKnownProviderTest extends OID4VCIssuerTestBase {

    @TestSetup
    public void configureTestRealmExt() {
        // do extended setup
    }
}

public abstract class OID4VCIssuerTestBase {

    @TestSetup
    public void configureTestRealm() {
        // do basic setup
    }
}
```

I see this call order ...

1. OID4VCIWellKnownProviderTest.configureTestRealmExt()
2. OID4VCIssuerTestBase.configureTestRealm()

It should be the other way around, shouldn't it?

Also, when I give both methods the same name, the sub-class method is called twice.

It should be possible to do this ...

```
    @TestSetup
    public void configureTestRealm() {
        super.configureTestRealm()

        // do extended setup
    }
```

### Version

latest

### Regression

- [ ] The issue is a regression

### Expected behavior

Call super class method before subclass method

or

Don't call super class method when overridden by subclass method

